You wrote . . .  &quot;To Betty:  I will gladly get a grip if you can tell me what alias lien got all riled up over?  My second post was in reaction to her going off at me with no basis that I was aware of.  Can you explain?  How did she ever decide that I did not respect her, or that respect was even an issue, or that I was a hostile stranger to her? Stranger, yes, but how or why would I be hostile to a stranger?  Kind of an oxymoron there.  I truly am at a loss, hence my final conclusion that her over-reaction had a political or secondary agenda.&quot;<br><br>
No one comes to this site without their own load of baggage: you have yours, Lien's got her's, and I have mine. As another woman I can empathize with Lien's unwillingness to put her E-mail address out for all to see.   (We aren't just talking about you guys who have been here posting, we are talking  ???? even after this site closes.)  Nurse Hands didn't give an E-mail address.   I didn't put an E-mail address out into a public cyberspace either.    Lien gave a name but chose not to give an E-mail address.  She explained in her April 19  3:18:59 Response why she didn't give a complete name and E-mail address.   In response to your &quot;I cannot respect someone who deliberately signs off as 'alias-lien' with no address.&quot;  She honestly tells you that she doesn't want unsolicited E-mail. So, how she got the idea that you did not respect her is that you told her so. She has gotten hit-on by the men who travel the information highway looking for women.   She never said you are  a white male fetishist.  Or that when she posted she expected you to send unsolicited messages.  She did say &quot;I don't like potentially hostile strangers knowing who I am or where they can reach me.&quot;   She said she considered you hostile in response to your response.  Re your comment  &quot;if you do not want 'potentially hostile strangers answering you,  then why do you ask questions?&quot;   Two different issues,  asking for opinion on the WWW versus having unsolicited opinions come in  to a personal mailbox.    Have you seen the movie &quot;The Net&quot; ? Scared the you know what out of me for months.<br><br>
Lien said your response made her feel that you are hostile toward her.  What did you say that could make her feel that way?   <br><br>
